Construct named list from parameter vector

Source: R/extractParams.R
paramsVec2list.Rd

Construct named list from parameter vector

Usage

paramsVec2list(
  THETA,
  DIM_EXT,
  NYB,
  NYA,
  N_GRADES,
  N_EXAMS,
  LABS_EXAMS = NULL,
  LABS_GRADES = NULL,
  LABS_COVARIATES = NULL
)

Arguments

THETA

Parameter vector. Structure to be documented.

DIM_EXT

number of external covariates in the competing risk model.

NYB

number of years in the non-graduatable state. Needed for determining how many time-related intercepts in the competing risk model.

NYA

number of years in the graduatable state. Needed for determining how many time-related intercepts in the competing risk model.

N_GRADES

number of grades modelled.

N_EXAMS

number of exams.

LABS_EXAMS

optional label for exams

LABS_GRADES

optional label for grades

LABS_COVARIATES

optional label for covariates

Value

Given a proper unconstrained parameter vector, it returns a list of the model parameters.

Examples


seed <- 123

## Setup dimensions
external_covariates <- 3L     # number of external covariates
years_before <- 6L            # number of possible years in the regime without graduation
years_after <- 2L             # number of possible years in the regime with graduation
grades <- 4L                  # number of grades
exams <- 10L                  # number of exams

dim <- 3 * (external_covariates+2) + 2 * (years_before) +
        years_after + 3 * exams + exams * grades + 2

set.seed(seed)
theta <- rnorm(dim)

## Retrieve the list
params_list <- paramsVec2list(
  THETA = theta,
  DIM_EXT = external_covariates,
  NYB = years_before,
  NYA = years_after,
  N_GRADES = grades,
  N_EXAMS = exams)
